𝐓𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐢𝐬 𝐦𝐞 //⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Transparent, raw & vulnerable.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I am to the point where I am sick of shame and yet it tries to suffocate me.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Shame that my body has a longer journey in this healing path than I desire.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Shame that my body gains weight back when I am not in perfection mode.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Shame that I can’t seem to white knuckle it long enough to see lasting results.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Shame that my best is behind me. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Shame that I am not enough.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Shame that my body doesn’t respond the way I want it to and treat it.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
// this journey is not my own. It’s the Lords and I pray I walk in His will and honor him with my words and actions.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I am weary from hiding the “flaws”⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I am weary of feeling like my love of wellness is invalid because I’m still here. Here in the waiting.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Here learning what it looks like to actively wait- that my waiting is not wasted.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
He is so good and faithful.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
However to be honest it’s not always feel like a comforting hand holding me. It’s messy and scary and confusing and yet here I am. Standing here exposed with my belly hanging over my leggings. My arms not as toned as they once were and cannot seem to eek out a smile today. Im quietly waiting in the Lord- He always guides, and he will continue to do so, it just may not look like I want it to.
.
.
.
.
♥️
